lyrics:
There was a man from White Church, his name was Philly More 
By the age of only twenty, he had his hair no more 
He used to rock it long, wild and free
But now he's sportin' that shiny dome, for all to see (ooh-yeah)
But he don't care, he's just showin' off his style


Oh Philly More, where'd your locks go? (where'd they go?)
You traded in your hair for that smooth, bald glow (shiny and bald)
But it don't matter, you're still rockin' the show (rockin' it)
Philly More, oh-oh, Philly More, woah-oh (you've got the groove)
